PMID== 11973144
TI  == the esat-6/wxg100 superfamily -- and a new gram-positive secretion system?
AB  == esat-6 is a small secreted protein of unknown function from mycobacterium tuberculosis that is of fundamental importance in virulence and protective immunity. a psi-blast search has identified distant homologues of esat-6 in more  tractable bacteria, including bacillus subtilis, bacillus anthracis, staphylococcus aureus and clostridium acetobutylicum. the genes for esat-6-like proteins often cluster with genes encoding homologues of b. subtilis yuka. i speculate that the esat-6-like and yuka-like proteins form a novel gram-positive  secretion system potentially driven by the ftsk/spoiiie atpase domains in the yuka-like proteins. the way is now open to investigate this hypothesis in organisms that are easier to manipulate than pathogenic mycobacteria.
